Title: Danfoss KVP22 solder evaporator pressure regulator 7/8"
Description: Intended to be mounted in the suction line after the evaporator, this Danfoss KVP22 evaporator pressure regulator with 7/8" solder ODF connections maintains a constant evaporating pressure and, in turn, ensures a constant surface temperature on the evaporator. With modulating regulation, the regulator throttles the suction line, matching refrigerant gas to the evaporator load. Closing when pressure inside the evaporator falls below a set value, this valve ensures that pressure doesn't fall to a lower level than required. It can allow for differentiation between evaporating pressures in two or more evaporators in a single compressor system.
category: Refrigeration/Controls/Refrigeration Valves/Refrigeration Pressure Regulating Valve/Refrigeration Pressure Regulating Valve.csv -> Danfoss KVP22 solder evaporator pressure regulator 7/8"

Title: Danfoss WVFX15 direct actuated valve 1/2" 3.5-16bar
Description: Regulating the flow of water in a refrigeration plant with water-cooled condensers, the Danfoss WVFX15 pressure operated water valve provides modulating regulation of condensing pressure within set limits. Suitable for use with flammable refrigerants, this valve shuts off the flow of cooling water when a refrigeration plant is stopped. With 1/2" threaded x 1/4" SAE flare connections, this valve ensures a double seal between refrigerant and water line, ensuring that should bellows be damaged, refrigerant won't leak into the water. This ensures that the valve can be used with a double walled heat exchanger and that the water circuit does not need to be considered part of the installation for flammable refrigerants per EN378-1:2008, clause 4.4.2.2.
